    stable 3.5 3.4 3.3 3.2 3.1 3.0
   require a52dec jpeg libavc1394 libdv libiec61883 libvorbis
  optional libquicktime '' '' for quicktime support
  category video
 attribute console
    source $SOURCEFORGE_URL kino/dvgrab/$VERSION/dvgrab-$VERSION.tar.gz
  homepage http://kino.schirmacher.de
  estimate 100
      desc 'command line IEEE1394 (firewire) video capture utility
dvgrab is a program which saves the audio and video data
from an IEEE (firewire) digital source (camcorder,
A/D video converter, digital VCR) into an AVI file.
These AVI files can then be processed further by other
video editing programs available for Windows or Linux.
The advantages of using dvgrab for creating the AVI files are:
* Autosplit features
* Several file formats (raw, dv1, dv2)
* Error recovery'
